item.title: 【Albums (lossless)】ALAC - Isabella Castillo | La Usurpadora: THE MUSICAL, THE MOVIE (Soundtrack) [Master/HiRes ALAC 24Bit/48kHz]
item.description:
La Usurpadora: The Musical (2023) is a comedy film & musical, basically like Disney’s High School Musical, filmed in Mexico & Las Vegas. The film stars Isabella Castillo, known internationally by her role of “Grachi” on the Nickelodeon TV series of the same title, she sings most of the songs. This film was recorded in spanish & english, but the songs are exclusively in spanish & it’s based on a heavily popular mexican telenovela of the same title “La Usurpadora”. This soundtrack contains covers of many latin popstars like Paulina Rubio, Gloria Estefan, Selena & more.

Fred again.. "Boiler Room - Fred again.. in London, July 29, 2022 (DJ Mix)"
Dolby Atmos Music



Frederick John Philip Gibson (born 19 July 1993),[1] known professionally as Fred Again (stylised as Fred again..) or simply Fred (stylised as FRED), is an English record producer, singer, songwriter, multi-instrumentalist and DJ. He frequently collaborates with other artists and in 2024 was nominated for Best New Artist at the 66th Annual Grammy Awards and won Best Dance/Electronic Album for Actual Life 3 (January 1 – September 9 2022) and Best Dance/Electronic Recording for "Rumble".
